@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Something went wrong";
    ViewData["BodyClass"] = "library-page";
}

@*
    Shared 5xx view. Reached three ways:
      1. UseExceptionHandler in Program.cs re-executes /error/500 on any
         uncaught exception in non-dev builds.
      2. The status-code re-execute fires when a controller returns a
         bare StatusCode(5xx) with no body.
      3. Controllers that detect an upstream failure at the top of an
         action can return View("ServerError") directly.
    Same layout shell as NotFound: page-header + two CTAs side-by-side.
    Copy intentionally vague — the user can't act on a stack trace and
    the developer details belong in server logs (which the exception
    handler middleware writes through the registered ILogger). Refresh
    sits in the primary slot since most 5xx today are transient
    upstream blips (AniList rate-limiting, Kitsu hiccups).
*@
<div class="page-header" style="text-align: center;">
    <h1 class="page-title">Something went wrong</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">An error occurred while processing your request. Try again in a moment — if the problem keeps happening, the upstream service may be down.</p>
</div>
<div class="hero-ctas" style="justify-content: center;">
    <a class="hero-cta hero-cta-primary" href="javascript:location.reload()">Retry</a>
    <a class="hero-cta hero-cta-secondary" href="/">Dashboard</a>
</div>
